WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
(Transcribed by TurboScribe.ai)

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.790
Hey everyone, welcome to this video where we explore

00:00:02.790 --> 00:00:06.130
Runway, a complete creative toolkit that uses the power

00:00:06.130 --> 00:00:09.376
of AI to generate and edit both images and videos.

00:00:09.690 --> 00:00:11.730
You can access it directly through your browser for

00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:14.650
free, making it easy to start creating without installing

00:00:14.650 --> 00:00:15.838
any software.

00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:26.120
First of all, log in with your Runway account

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:29.720
to access the homepage where you'll find several options

00:00:29.720 --> 00:00:30.280
on the right.

00:00:31.280 --> 00:00:34.380
On the left side, you'll see Sessions, which include

00:00:34.380 --> 00:00:36.280
all your projects in progress.

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:41.140
Below that, under Assets, you'll find all files uploaded

00:00:41.140 --> 00:00:43.160
or generated inside Runway.

00:00:44.120 --> 00:00:46.880
Farther down, under Create, you'll get a list of

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.660
all the AI generation tools.

00:00:49.200 --> 00:00:51.880
You can also go to All Tools to view

00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:54.820
the complete set of AI features available in Runway.

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:58.640
To begin generating, you can either go to Start

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:01.100
a Session in the bottom left corner, or use

00:01:01.100 --> 00:01:03.280
the chatbot located at the top of the homepage.

00:01:03.920 --> 00:01:07.220
For example, if we go to Start a Session,

00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:10.120
you can use this workspace or switch to Chat

00:01:10.120 --> 00:01:12.480
Mode at the top to return to the chatbot

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:13.680
view we saw earlier.

00:01:14.920 --> 00:01:16.520
Let's start with chat mode.

00:01:17.060 --> 00:01:19.560
You can request an image, like a blonde horse

00:01:19.560 --> 00:01:21.680
running in the desert, or even a video.

00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:25.360
You can also upload images to use as references.

00:01:26.320 --> 00:01:28.180
To begin, click Ask on the right.

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:31.520
Make sure your prompts are direct, clear, and free

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:33.200
of loops or negative phrases.

00:01:33.960 --> 00:01:37.880
Always provide specific, straightforward details to guide the AI.

00:01:38.780 --> 00:01:41.560
The generation is powered by Runway's newest model,

00:01:41.560 --> 00:01:43.960
Gen-4, which we'll look at more closely later.

00:01:44.880 --> 00:01:47.680
Once the generation is complete, the AI will suggest

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:49.020
several follow-up options.

00:01:49.460 --> 00:01:51.460
This is helpful if you're just starting with AI

00:01:51.460 --> 00:01:53.720
tools or don't yet know how to get the

00:01:53.720 --> 00:01:54.840
best results.

00:01:54.940 --> 00:01:57.180
For example, you can pick one of the suggestions,

00:01:57.660 --> 00:02:00.320
like option 1, to restyle the image and do

00:02:00.320 --> 00:02:00.860
a cartoon.

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:03.940
And here's the result.

00:02:05.500 --> 00:02:08.340
We're still in Chat Mode, but we can switch

00:02:08.340 --> 00:02:11.740
to the standard session interface, also called Tool Mode,

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:13.620
by clicking in the top left corner.

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:18.000
This view is more advanced, ideal for users with

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:19.140
some AI experience.

00:02:19.700 --> 00:02:22.400
On the left, you'll see all input controls to

00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:23.600
guide your next generation.

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:26.560
And on the right, you'll find your past results

00:02:26.560 --> 00:02:27.440
from chat mode.

00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:30.580
In the top left, you can choose whether to

00:02:30.580 --> 00:02:32.000
generate an image or a video.

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:34.620
For now, we'll stick with video generation.

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:38.155
At the bottom, you can switch the AI model being used.

00:02:38.540 --> 00:02:41.600
Currently, Runway supports the latest Gen-4 model and

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:42.840
the earlier Gen-3.

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:45.860
Gen-1 and Gen-2 are no longer available

00:02:45.860 --> 00:02:46.740
in the newest version.

00:02:47.590 --> 00:02:49.680
So now, let's start generating a video.

00:02:50.240 --> 00:02:53.260
We will begin using Gen-4 Turbo, one of

00:02:53.260 --> 00:02:54.940
the best models for video generation.

00:02:55.400 --> 00:02:59.240
Great for live actions, VFX, and motion clips.

00:02:59.660 --> 00:03:03.001
It's especially useful if you need to animate simple images,

00:03:03.001 --> 00:03:06.848
or you don't need to create very complex  videos.

00:03:07.140 --> 00:03:10.360
This generation model requires an image to use as

00:03:10.360 --> 00:03:11.011
a reference.

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:14.075
You can select one you own from the Assets folder.

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:17.360
Or go to Create Image to generate one with

00:03:17.360 --> 00:03:18.440
AI right away.

00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:21.660
You can also use the last image you created

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:24.440
by clicking on Input for Video in the bottom

00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:25.849
left corner.

00:03:27.360 --> 00:03:29.220
Then crop the reference image if needed.

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:33.420
In the prompt box at the bottom, describe what

00:03:33.420 --> 00:03:34.380
you want in the video.

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.140
For example, a blonde horse running with powerful movement.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:42.240
Here, describe the main subject, how it moves, its

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:45.380
actions, any mood, and even camera movement.

00:03:46.820 --> 00:03:50.060
For example, camera tracks the horse while it runs,

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:51.760
to follow the subject's motion.

00:03:53.080 --> 00:03:56.780
So, after defining the subject and camera movement, describe

00:03:56.780 --> 00:03:58.020
the scene or background.

00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:02.440
For example, the desert remains static, only sand dust

00:04:02.440 --> 00:04:03.835
rises behind.

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:05.520
Then define the style.

00:04:06.020 --> 00:04:08.080
For example, cinematic or realistic.

00:04:08.640 --> 00:04:11.980
You can also choose cartoon, 3D animation, and more.

00:04:12.760 --> 00:04:14.980
You can find more guidance in the video description

00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:17.640
by checking the official documentation of Runway.

00:04:18.500 --> 00:04:21.180
Below the image preview, you'll find other options.

00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:22.940
For now, let's skip Act Two.

00:04:23.040 --> 00:04:24.260
We will explore it shortly.

00:04:24.900 --> 00:04:27.380
On the right, set the video aspect ratio.

00:04:28.860 --> 00:04:31.280
At the bottom, choose the total video length.

00:04:31.580 --> 00:04:32.840
Let's go with 5 seconds.

00:04:33.400 --> 00:04:37.008
Then click Generate to create the video using Gen-4 Turbo.

00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:40.340
The result will be in 720p resolution.

00:04:40.740 --> 00:04:42.900
Use the player below to preview the final video.

00:04:43.940 --> 00:04:46.420
At the top, you'll see the full generation info,

00:04:46.880 --> 00:04:49.520
the model used, the reference image, the full prompt,

00:04:49.780 --> 00:04:51.160
and other editable settings.

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:57.100
At the bottom, you get additional tools, like restyling

00:04:57.100 --> 00:04:59.780
the video, using the current frame as a reference

00:04:59.780 --> 00:05:02.680
for another video, and other features we'll cover later.

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:06.820
You can also download the video in 720p at

00:05:06.820 --> 00:05:08.420
24 frames per second.

00:05:09.700 --> 00:05:13.180
You can also upscale the video to 4K resolution

00:05:13.180 --> 00:05:16.020
by spending 10 credits with this 4K button.

00:05:17.320 --> 00:05:20.838
The copyright of any generated media is fully owned by you.

00:05:21.260 --> 00:05:24.160
Runway allows you to use these videos freely, including

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:25.300
for commercial purposes.

00:05:26.620 --> 00:05:28.460
Each generation consumes credits.

00:05:28.840 --> 00:05:32.446
You'll start with 125 credits if you're using the free plan.

00:05:32.680 --> 00:05:35.300
And receive more depending on your subscription plan.

00:05:35.920 --> 00:05:38.360
Credits are used based on what you generate, either

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:40.760
an image or a video, and on the model

00:05:40.760 --> 00:05:42.120
selected for the generation.

00:05:42.760 --> 00:05:46.640
Consider a subscription to receive monthly credits, remove watermarks,

00:05:46.960 --> 00:05:50.220
and unlock premium options like upscaling to 4K.

00:05:51.580 --> 00:05:54.720
Currently, Runway doesn't offer tools to increase the frame

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:57.560
rate of videos, which remain fixed at 24 frames

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:58.841
per second.

00:05:58.920 --> 00:06:02.380
If Gen-4 Turbo isn't enough, for more complex

00:06:02.380 --> 00:06:05.200
tasks, you can switch to Gen-4, the most

00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:07.040
powerful model available in Runway.

00:06:07.520 --> 00:06:10.440
This model is available with paid plans only and

00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:14.012
provides better consistency for characters and stronger

00:06:14.012 --> 00:06:15.011
alignment with reference images.

00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:21.010
So, for example, we can upload an image, and

00:06:21.010 --> 00:06:23.130
then define a prompt, which is optional.

00:06:24.490 --> 00:06:27.530
Set all the options below, such as aspect ratio

00:06:27.530 --> 00:06:30.510
and video duration, then click Generate.

00:06:35.400 --> 00:06:37.600
With Gen-4, you can use Runway Aleph to

00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:39.940
edit an existing video up to its first 5

00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:43.640
seconds, switch to Chat Mode to generate one from

00:06:43.640 --> 00:06:45.860
scratch, and get assistance from AI.

00:06:46.660 --> 00:06:49.180
Or go to Edit with Aleph to modify a

00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:50.700
generated video on the right.

00:06:52.460 --> 00:06:55.080
Describe how you want to edit the video, such

00:06:55.080 --> 00:06:58.400
as changing the camera angle, adjusting the lighting, switching

00:06:58.400 --> 00:07:01.040
the weather, or adding and removing details.

00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:07.320
Use simple instructions like Add, Remove, Change, or Replace.

00:07:08.060 --> 00:07:11.020
For example, let's replace the horse with a fire

00:07:11.020 --> 00:07:13.480
horse, then go to Generate.

00:07:19.250 --> 00:07:20.990
If you want, you can also add a reference

00:07:20.990 --> 00:07:23.510
image, by using the Upload button above to guide

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:24.850
the editing more precisely.

00:07:32.150 --> 00:07:34.330
You can also switch to the older Gen-3

00:07:34.330 --> 00:07:37.627
Alpha Turbo to test things out while using fewer credits.

00:07:38.150 --> 00:07:42.839
This model offers extra control with more settings below.

00:07:43.006 --> 00:07:45.210
If we go to Text Prompt, we can define

00:07:45.210 --> 00:07:47.610
what we want to generate, supported by either an

00:07:47.610 --> 00:07:49.430
image or a video as reference.

00:07:50.670 --> 00:07:54.147
For example, let's upload this portrait image and crop it.

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:01.120
Then, let's write a prompt to describe the video

00:08:01.120 --> 00:08:03.400
like we did during the Gen-4 generation.

00:08:04.360 --> 00:08:06.260
At the bottom, select the aspect ratio.

00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:07.360
We'll use Portrait.

00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:11.660
In Settings, recheck the aspect ratio and check the

00:08:11.660 --> 00:08:14.040
video resolution, which remains at 720p.

00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:18.160
Now, set the video length up to 10 seconds,

00:08:18.160 --> 00:08:19.620
and click Generate.

00:08:20.760 --> 00:08:21.940
Let's check the result.

00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:25.840
This complex prompt didn't work as expected because Gen-3

00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:28.600
is a simpler model, so we should switch

00:08:28.600 --> 00:08:30.220
to Gen-4 to get better results.

00:08:31.039 --> 00:08:34.020
You also have the Extend button here, which lets

00:08:34.020 --> 00:08:36.545
you add 8 more seconds by entering a new prompt.

00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:41.700
Other available options include upscaling to 4K and downloading

00:08:41.700 --> 00:08:43.960
the result, just like with Gen-4.

00:08:44.980 --> 00:08:48.460
You can also use keyframes to control video motion

00:08:48.460 --> 00:08:51.460
over time, keeping the same style as the first

00:08:51.460 --> 00:08:52.460
keyframe you've added.

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:55.680
You define one image as the first keyframe and

00:08:55.680 --> 00:08:56.980
then add two more if you want.

00:08:58.560 --> 00:09:01.500
For example, a central keyframe and a final one

00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:03.000
to end the generated video.

00:09:06.310 --> 00:09:07.710
Let's update the prompt description.

00:09:08.570 --> 00:09:11.410
Then, switch to Camera Control at the bottom to

00:09:11.410 --> 00:09:12.730
also manage camera movement.

00:09:13.310 --> 00:09:16.170
For example, add effects like panning or tilting.

00:09:16.630 --> 00:09:19.530
These camera settings apply to the entire video, not

00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:22.350
just a single keyframe, even if the preview shows

00:09:22.350 --> 00:09:23.450
only one at the top.

00:09:25.910 --> 00:09:28.530
You can also describe camera movement directly in the

00:09:28.530 --> 00:09:29.835
text prompt.

00:09:30.270 --> 00:09:32.310
Now, hit Generate to see the result.

00:09:35.730 --> 00:09:38.650
Sometimes the generation may jump to the last keyframe

00:09:38.650 --> 00:09:41.530
too quickly if it looks very different from the

00:09:41.530 --> 00:09:45.070
others, so try using keyframes with similar content to

00:09:45.070 --> 00:09:46.050
keep results smooth.

00:09:47.130 --> 00:09:49.790
At the bottom, you also have the Act One

00:09:49.790 --> 00:09:52.270
option, which we'll explore later in this video.

00:09:52.850 --> 00:09:55.130
You'll also find the Expand feature, which lets you

00:09:55.130 --> 00:09:57.270
change the aspect ratio of any video.

00:09:58.210 --> 00:10:00.890
For example, you can pick a video above or select

00:10:00.890 --> 00:10:04.757
the latest one under Actions, then click Expand Video.

00:10:05.510 --> 00:10:07.950
In this case, we have a portrait layout, so

00:10:07.950 --> 00:10:09.350
let's convert it to landscape.

00:10:10.390 --> 00:10:13.030
You'll see the change from here to here.

00:10:18.100 --> 00:10:20.660
If Gen-3 Alpha Turbo doesn't meet your needs,

00:10:20.800 --> 00:10:23.220
you can switch to Gen-3 Alpha, which offers

00:10:23.220 --> 00:10:23.980
higher precision.

00:10:23.980 --> 00:10:26.700
It's more affordable than the Gen-4 model and

00:10:26.700 --> 00:10:28.680
is only available with a paid plan.

00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:31.860
Unlike Gen-3 Alpha Turbo, this model lets you

00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:34.320
generate a video using just a text prompt.

00:10:34.920 --> 00:10:37.820
You can optionally add an image or video as

00:10:37.820 --> 00:10:39.260
reference for extra detail.

00:10:40.420 --> 00:10:43.120
Just like Gen-4, Gen-3 Alpha performs better

00:10:43.120 --> 00:10:46.640
with detailed prompts, especially when you don't use a

00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:49.620
reference image, so your text needs to fully guide

00:10:49.620 --> 00:10:50.836
the output.

00:10:55.410 --> 00:10:57.670
You can also insert an image as a reference.

00:11:00.550 --> 00:11:03.475
And use it either as the first or last keyframe.

00:11:04.210 --> 00:11:06.656
This is great for adding motion to a static image.

00:11:08.230 --> 00:11:10.970
Now, let's see how to generate images with Runway.

00:11:11.390 --> 00:11:13.630
Just switch to Image from the top left corner.

00:11:14.130 --> 00:11:17.514
To make these images, Runway uses the ultimate Gen-4 model.

00:11:18.270 --> 00:11:20.690
You can use this feature to create characters or

00:11:20.690 --> 00:11:24.790
impressive landscapes, even complex ones, before moving on to

00:11:24.790 --> 00:11:25.570
generate a video.

00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:28.870
At the top, type a prompt describing what you

00:11:28.870 --> 00:11:33.570
want, include the subject, actions, background, colors, and of

00:11:33.570 --> 00:11:34.530
course, the style.

00:11:35.130 --> 00:11:37.570
At the bottom, if you don't use any reference,

00:11:37.850 --> 00:11:40.650
you can pick any style template to apply, like

00:11:40.650 --> 00:11:42.170
Vivid or High Contrast.

00:11:43.030 --> 00:11:45.890
Set the aspect ratio, the number of image variations

00:11:45.890 --> 00:11:50.110
to create, and also the resolution, between 720p or

00:11:50.110 --> 00:11:51.003
1080p.

00:11:51.710 --> 00:11:54.950
For more complex outputs, you can add image references

00:11:54.950 --> 00:11:56.270
by clicking right here.

00:11:57.450 --> 00:12:00.270
Under References, you can upload any image you have.

00:12:00.910 --> 00:12:02.490
For example, let's upload this one.

00:12:05.330 --> 00:12:08.310
Then, we can add two more, like a jaguar

00:12:08.310 --> 00:12:10.250
fur pattern and a specific landscape.

00:12:11.770 --> 00:12:14.050
You can also give each reference a name for

00:12:14.050 --> 00:12:16.270
more precise control when writing the prompt.

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:20.290
For example, name this one 'Lion', this one 'Jaguar

00:12:20.290 --> 00:12:22.630
Pattern', and this one 'Vulcan'.

00:12:23.350 --> 00:12:25.950
Then, in the prompt, use the @ symbol to

00:12:25.950 --> 00:12:27.910
refer to any of these specifically.

00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:30.410
Like selecting the Lion as the main subject.

00:12:31.430 --> 00:12:34.834
We can describe its skin by adding @JaguarPattern

00:12:34.834 --> 00:12:38.650
as skin and define the environment by using

00:12:38.650 --> 00:12:39.590
the Vulcan reference.

00:12:40.930 --> 00:12:42.130
This looks really good.

00:12:42.650 --> 00:12:45.990
If the results don't match your expectations, consider adding

00:12:45.990 --> 00:12:49.630
more detail from the image references by using the

00:12:49.630 --> 00:12:50.650
Generate Prompt feature.

00:12:51.810 --> 00:12:54.430
Now, this image becomes the reference for the next

00:12:54.430 --> 00:12:55.370
video we'll create.

00:12:56.110 --> 00:12:58.170
So go back to Video from the top left,

00:12:58.590 --> 00:13:03.250
clear any previous references and prompts, and select this

00:13:03.250 --> 00:13:05.310
new image under Input for Video.

00:13:06.390 --> 00:13:09.010
Since this is a complex image with specific features

00:13:09.010 --> 00:13:11.430
like the jaguar fur, it's better to switch to

00:13:11.430 --> 00:13:15.070
the Gen-4 model, which ensures the subject stays consistent.

00:13:15.790 --> 00:13:17.830
Now start describing what's going to happen.

00:13:18.210 --> 00:13:22.090
Include the subject, its actions, the camera motion, the

00:13:22.090 --> 00:13:23.510
scene, and the style.

00:13:24.270 --> 00:13:25.710
Then click Generate.

00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:32.220
This shows how the video generation can be very

00:13:32.220 --> 00:13:34.900
precise even when using a complex reference image.

00:13:35.700 --> 00:13:37.740
You can download any image you generate with the

00:13:37.740 --> 00:13:39.140
button in the bottom right corner.

00:13:40.040 --> 00:13:43.020
Then, back on the home page, among the tools

00:13:43.020 --> 00:13:45.960
list, you can go to Upscale Image to upload

00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:50.680
the image you just created and upscale its resolution

00:13:50.680 --> 00:13:54.360
up to HD, 2K, or even 4K.

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.980
Keep in mind that video generations will always stay

00:13:57.980 --> 00:14:01.160
at 720p, even if you use a 4K image

00:14:01.160 --> 00:14:02.013
as a reference.

00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:05.860
This image generator is very useful for creating consistent

00:14:05.860 --> 00:14:09.060
characters and videos thanks to the references and the

00:14:09.060 --> 00:14:10.380
@ symbols you can use.

00:14:11.040 --> 00:14:14.060
You can select the images again, update the prompt,

00:14:17.430 --> 00:14:19.850
and generate a new image while keeping the character

00:14:19.850 --> 00:14:20.847
consistent.

00:14:20.890 --> 00:14:21.850
And here it is.

00:14:22.270 --> 00:14:23.210
This is the result.

00:14:24.150 --> 00:14:27.910
On the video generation session, switch to Act Two

00:14:27.910 --> 00:14:29.630
at the bottom if you want to provide a

00:14:29.630 --> 00:14:31.630
video reference for your character to follow.

00:14:32.610 --> 00:14:35.270
You can either record yourself or upload a video

00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:39.182
to capture gestures of the face, hands, and full body.

00:14:40.090 --> 00:14:44.961
'No, no, no. Understood?'

00:14:45.850 --> 00:14:49.070
Just below, upload your character, which can be either

00:14:49.070 --> 00:14:52.330
an image or a video, for example, a lion.

00:14:53.370 --> 00:14:58.570
Set the options including aspect ratio, expressiveness,

00:14:58.570 --> 00:15:00.630
and whether to transfer gestures from the reference.

00:15:02.150 --> 00:15:04.850
The output video will last as long as the

00:15:04.850 --> 00:15:06.030
reference video provided.

00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:13.987
'No, no, no. Understood?'

00:15:14.740 --> 00:15:17.300
If you only need facial expressions, you can switch

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:20.465
to Gen-3 Alpha Turbo and use Act One instead.

00:15:20.980 --> 00:15:23.160
Keep in mind it will depreciate in the future.

00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:26.000
To learn more about Act One, check our previous

00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:27.040
tutorial on Runway.

00:15:28.280 --> 00:15:30.820
If you need to add a voice, open Generative

00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:33.100
Audio and go to Lip Sync Video.

00:15:33.940 --> 00:15:36.560
Import the video of your character or pick any

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:37.860
template available in Runway.

00:15:38.620 --> 00:15:41.260
This will be analyzed to detect faces, though it

00:15:41.260 --> 00:15:42.780
mainly works on human faces.

00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:46.580
At this point, upload any audio file or simply

00:15:46.580 --> 00:15:48.000
type the text you want spoken.

00:15:48.720 --> 00:15:51.140
Choose a voice by clicking on the microphone button.

00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:53.840
'I'd like to tell you a story.'

00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:56.100
Then hit Generate to get the final result.

00:15:57.040 --> 00:15:58.560
'Welcome to this new world of AI.'

00:16:00.320 --> 00:16:02.040
Now let's see the sketch feature.

00:16:02.500 --> 00:16:04.560
Let's use a simple tree as the image reference.

00:16:05.680 --> 00:16:07.500
Give it a name, as we did with the

00:16:07.500 --> 00:16:10.824
lion, and then click the brush button to add a sketch.

00:16:12.020 --> 00:16:14.900
At the bottom, you'll find tools to draw simple

00:16:14.900 --> 00:16:17.120
shapes or paint directly on the image.

00:16:17.680 --> 00:16:19.940
For example, let's draw a cracked ground.

00:16:19.940 --> 00:16:23.000
If you pick a wrong color, use CTRL or

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:25.620
CMD and Z to undo your action.

00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:29.420
And retry by changing the stroke color to black.

00:16:32.100 --> 00:16:34.680
When ready, go to Export Sketch to use this

00:16:34.680 --> 00:16:36.000
reference along with a prompt.

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:40.540
After sketching, update the name, add a supporting prompt,

00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:42.500
and click Generate.

00:16:42.900 --> 00:16:44.014
Here's the result.

00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:47.600
You can also ask the Gen-4 model to

00:16:47.600 --> 00:16:49.240
remove the background from an image.

00:16:50.520 --> 00:16:54.320
Another option is to apply very specific modifications to

00:16:54.320 --> 00:16:55.560
parts of the reference image.

00:16:56.160 --> 00:16:58.940
For example, go to Sketch, choose a color that

00:16:58.940 --> 00:17:02.100
stands out, like pink, and tell the AI to

00:17:02.100 --> 00:17:02.960
pull down a branch.

00:17:03.619 --> 00:17:05.740
Draw a simple arrow and add a label for

00:17:05.740 --> 00:17:07.380
additional clarity of how to edit.

00:17:11.560 --> 00:17:15.140
Then go to Export Sketch and either generate as-is

00:17:15.140 --> 00:17:17.060
or support it with a prompt.

00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:20.000
This is the result of the generation.

00:17:20.859 --> 00:17:24.160
The same Sketch tool can create interesting camera shots.

00:17:26.369 --> 00:17:27.369
Thanks for watching this video!

00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:29.770
Make sure to visit our YouTube channel and our

00:17:29.770 --> 00:17:32.690
official website to discover more tips and free guides

00:17:32.690 --> 00:17:34.590
on artificial intelligence platforms!

